images.description: Liftoff of unmanned Saturn I mission SA-9 from Complex 37.  SA-9 carried the first Pegasus meteoroid detection satellite.
Apollo spacecraft CSM-002 atop a Little Joe II launch vehicle at White Sands Missile Range
Apollo boilerplate spacecraft BP-22 is being checked out before launch of Apollo missiob A-003 (Apollo High Altitude Abort) from White Sands Missile Range
Portrait of Dr. Werner von Braun
Launch of Apollo mission A-003 (Apollo High Altitude Abort) from complex 36 at White Sands Missile Range in New Mexico
View of recovery of Apollo boilerplate spacecraft BP-22 after launch of Apollo High Altitude Abort from White Sands Missile Range
Night launch of unmanned SA-8 mission
Little Joe II launch vehicle, carrying Apollo Command Module Boilerplate 22 malfunctioned during a test of the escape system, 05/19/65.
Launch of Saturn SA-8, carrying the second Pegasus meteoroid detection satellite, from complex 37 of the Kennedy Space Center
Von Braun and others react with excitement to the launch of SA-8

Time exposure of the launch of Saturn SA-8, carrying Pegasus-2 spacecraft. Prominent features of the Merritt Island Launch Area - the Vehicle Assembly Building and three Launcher Umbilical Towers - are seen in the background.
41-second test firing of all five engines of the Saturn V S-IC stage
Apollo Pad Abort Test #2
Launch of Apollo Pad Abort test 2.
Recovery of Apollo boilerplate spacecraft BP-23A after Pad Abort 2.
Boilerplate 23A Command Module after Pad Abort Test #2
Apollo boilerplate spacecraft and Pegasus-3 spacecraft are being mated to Saturn booster SA-10 at launch complex 37
Launch of Saturn SA-10, carrying Apollo boilerplate spacecraft and Pegasus-3 satellite.
Apollo spacecraft 002 is being erected for mating with Little Joe II launcher in preparation for Apollo Intermediate Altitude Abort at White Sands Missile Range.
Flight controllers, including Gene Kranz (front left)  and Chris Kraft (front right)
